      "source": [
        "## Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "MaxDiff, also called Best-Worst Scaling, is a survey method for measuring relative preferences. Instead of asking people to rate every item on a numeric scale, each respondent sees a small set of items and chooses the one they like most and the one they like least. In this survey, each task shows four MSBA classes from UCSD Rady, and the respondent selects the most-preferred and least-preferred class from that set.\n",
        "\n",
        "MaxDiff is useful because people are usually better at making direct trade-offs than at calibrating a 1-to-10 rating scale. One person's \"8 out of 10\" may not mean the same thing as another person's \"8 out of 10,\" but choosing a best and worst option forces real differentiation among the items shown together. This helps avoid scale-use bias and makes the results easier to compare across respondents.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this analysis, the items are the 10 core MSBA classes. I estimate class preferences in three ways. First, I use a simple counts analysis: the percent of times each class is picked best minus the percent of times it is picked worst. Second, I fit a multinomial logit model, or MNL model, using maximum likelihood. Third, I fit the same MNL model using Bayesian methods with a random-walk Metropolis-Hastings sampler. I expect the three methods to agree on the broad ranking of classes, especially at the top and bottom, but they differ in how they quantify the strength of preference and how they communicate uncertainty.\n",
        "\n",
        "## The Data"
      ],
      "id": "b0f845f8"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: read-and-clean-data\n",
        "#| echo: false\n",
        "# Keep both CSV files in the same folder as this .qmd file.\n",
        "design_all = pd.read_csv(\"maxdiff_design_and_choices.csv\")\n",
        "labels_raw = pd.read_csv(\"maxdiff_item_labels.csv\")\n",
        "design_all.columns = clean_colnames(design_all.columns)\n",
        "\n",
        "required_cols = {\"record_id\", \"task\", \"position\", \"item\", \"response\"}\n",
        "missing = required_cols - set(design_all.columns)\n",
        "if missing:\n",
        "    raise ValueError(f\"Missing required columns in design file: {missing}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "design_all = design_all[[\"record_id\", \"task\", \"position\", \"item\", \"response\"]].copy()\n",
        "design_all[\"record_id\"] = design_all[\"record_id\"].astype(str)\n",
        "for c in [\"task\", \"position\", \"item\", \"response\"]:\n",
        "    design_all[c] = design_all[c].astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# The labels file uses column 1 as the item number and column 2 as the class label.\n",
        "labels = labels_raw.iloc[:, :2].copy()\n",
        "labels.columns = [\"item\", \"item_label\"]\n",
        "labels = labels.dropna(subset=[\"item\", \"item_label\"])\n",
        "labels[\"item\"] = labels[\"item\"].astype(int)\n",
        "labels[\"item_label\"] = labels[\"item_label\"].astype(str)\n",
        "labels = labels.sort_values(\"item\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "labels[\"item_idx\"] = np.arange(len(labels))\n",
        "labels[\"class_short\"] = labels[\"item_label\"].str.replace(r\"\\s*\\(.*\\)$\", \"\", regex=True)\n",
        "labels[\"plot_label\"] = labels[\"class_short\"].map(compact_class_label)\n",
        "\n",
        "item_map = labels.copy()\n",
        "J_total = len(item_map)\n",
        "valid_items = set(item_map[\"item\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "design_labeled = design_all[design_all[\"item\"].isin(valid_items)].merge(\n",
        "    item_map, on=\"item\", how=\"left\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "screen_check = (\n",
        "    design_labeled\n",
        "    .groupby([\"record_id\", \"task\"])\n",
        "    .agg(\n",
        "        rows=(\"response\", \"size\"),\n",
        "        n_best=(\"response\", lambda x: (x == 1).sum()),\n",
        "        n_worst=(\"response\", lambda x: (x == -1).sum()),\n",
        "        n_neither=(\"response\", lambda x: (x == 0).sum()),\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "valid_screens = screen_check.query(\n",
        "    \"rows == 4 and n_best == 1 and n_worst == 1 and n_neither == 2\"\n",
        ")[[\"record_id\", \"task\"]]\n",
        "\n",
        "design = design_labeled.merge(valid_screens, on=[\"record_id\", \"task\"], how=\"inner\")\n",
        "\n",
        "raw_task_check = (\n",
        "    design_all\n",
        "    .groupby([\"record_id\", \"task\"])\n",
        "    .agg(\n",
        "        raw_rows=(\"response\", \"size\"),\n",
        "        raw_best=(\"response\", lambda x: (x == 1).sum()),\n",
        "        raw_worst=(\"response\", lambda x: (x == -1).sum()),\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "unlabeled_items = sorted(set(design_all[\"item\"]) - valid_items)"
      ],
      "id": "read-and-clean-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
