      "source": [
        "## From MaxDiff Data to MNL Choices\n",
        "\n",
        "The MaxDiff data can also be treated as multinomial logit choice data. The MNL model assigns each item $j$ a utility coefficient $\\beta_j$. If a task shows items $\\{a, b, c, d\\}$, the probability that item $b$ is chosen as best is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "P(\\text{best} = b) =\n",
        "\\frac{\\exp(\\beta_b)}\n",
        "{\\exp(\\beta_a) + \\exp(\\beta_b) + \\exp(\\beta_c) + \\exp(\\beta_d)}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "After the best item is selected, the worst item is chosen from the remaining three items. Since the worst item is the least preferred item, the utilities are flipped:\n",
