        "$$\n",
        "P(\\text{worst} = c \\mid \\text{best} = b) =\n",
        "\\frac{\\exp(-\\beta_c)}\n",
        "{\\exp(-\\beta_a) + \\exp(-\\beta_c) + \\exp(-\\beta_d)}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore, each MaxDiff task contributes two MNL-style observations: one best choice from the full set of four items, and one conditional worst choice from the remaining three items.\n",
        "\n",
        "The model is identified only up to an additive constant. If the same constant is added to every $\\beta$, the soft-max probabilities do not change. I therefore normalize the first class to have $\\beta_1 = 0$ and estimate the other coefficients relative to that reference class."
