        "## MNL via Bayesian Estimation\n",
        "\n",
        "The Bayesian version uses the same likelihood but adds a prior distribution over the free $\\beta$ parameters:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\pi(\\boldsymbol{\\beta} \\mid \\boldsymbol{y})\n",
        "\\propto\n",
        "L(\\boldsymbol{\\beta})\\pi(\\boldsymbol{\\beta}).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "I use a weakly informative normal prior,\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\boldsymbol{\\beta} \\sim N(\\boldsymbol{0}, 10I).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This prior is centered at zero and has standard deviation $\\sqrt{10} \\approx 3.16$, which is broad enough to be weakly informative on the utility scale.\n",
        "\n",
        "The following code is the core Bayesian model code. It defines the posterior and runs a random-walk Metropolis-Hastings sampler. It is shown because it is the main Bayesian estimation algorithm."
      ],
      "id": "f4c2ec48"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: bayes-core-code\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "prior_sd = np.sqrt(10.0)\n",
        "log_prior_const = -0.5 * (J_total - 1) * np.log(2 * np.pi * prior_sd**2)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def log_posterior(theta):\n",
        "    theta = np.asarray(theta)\n",
        "    return loglik(theta) + log_prior_const - 0.5 * np.sum(theta**2) / prior_sd**2\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def mh_sampler(theta0, n_iter, step, seed=1234):\n",
        "    local_rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n",
        "    theta = np.array(theta0, dtype=float).copy()\n",
        "    K = len(theta)\n",
        "    draws = np.empty((n_iter, K))\n",
        "    lp = log_posterior(theta)\n",
        "    accept = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    for t in range(n_iter):\n",
        "        proposal = theta + local_rng.normal(0, step, size=K)\n",
        "        lp_proposal = log_posterior(proposal)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if np.log(local_rng.random()) < lp_proposal - lp:\n",
        "            theta = proposal\n",
        "            lp = lp_proposal\n",
        "            accept += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "        draws[t, :] = theta\n",
        "\n",
        "    return draws, accept / n_iter\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def tune_step(theta0, start_step=0.08, n_pilot=2000, max_rounds=6):\n",
        "    step = start_step\n",
        "    current = np.array(theta0, dtype=float).copy()\n",
        "    history = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for r in range(max_rounds):\n",
        "        pilot_draws, ar = mh_sampler(current, n_pilot, step, seed=9000 + r)\n",
        "        current = pilot_draws[-1]\n",
        "        history.append({\"round\": r + 1, \"step\": step, \"accept_rate\": ar})\n",
        "\n",
        "        if 0.25 <= ar <= 0.40:\n",
        "            break\n",
        "        elif ar < 0.25:\n",
        "            step = step / 2\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            step = step * 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    return step, current, pd.DataFrame(history)"
      ],
      "id": "bayes-core-code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
